text.tspan: This visualisation shows the distribution of grants made by 47 grantmakers according to the relative deprivation of the recipients of each
Each shape shows how grants have been allocated - a fatter bottom indicates more grants have been awarded to recipients in more deprived
areas. A fatter head indicates more grants have been awarded to recipients in less deprived areas.
Data: Grant data from 360Giving / GrantNav, where the recipients postcode is supplied with the grant, and was successfully matched to a
lower layer super output area (~53,000 grants)
